  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HFC phase-down plan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the outcomes of the 80th Meeting of the Executive Committee of the Multilateral Fund for the Implementation of the Montreal Protocol and subsequently Decision 80/50(d), funding was approved for North Macedonia for Enabling Activities (EA) for HFC phase-down towards the early ratification of the Kigali Amendment. The main objective of the EA project was to prepare North Macedonia for the ratification and early implementation of the Kigali Amendment to the Montreal Protocol, considering the situation in the country with regard to the current HFC consumption. Legal documents, stakeholder engagement, and awareness raising events are in progress, which led to the ratification of the Kigali Amendment in February 2020.</narrative>
  </description>
